      "term": "Frangipane",
      "definition": "A rich almond cream made from ground almonds, butter, sugar, and eggs. When baked, frangipane sets to a moist, dense sponge with a slightly springy texture. It is the traditional filling of a Bakewell tart and many other almond-based pastries."
