          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " needs a fully cold pastry case before it goes in; a warm case will start cooking the bottom of the frangipane before the rest of the filling is ready. Blind-bake the case, cool it completely, then spread with jam and top with frangipane. The frangipane will rise and puff during baking and settle back to a dense, moist layer as it cools."
