            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make and blind-bake the pastry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rub the cold butter into the flour and icing sugar until fine crumbs form. Add the egg yolk and cold water; mix to a dough. Flatten, wrap, and refrigerate for 20 minutes. Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Roll the pastry to 3 mm and line a 23 cm tart tin. Refrigerate for 10 minutes. Line the case with scrunched baking paper, fill with baking beans or rice, and blind-bake for 15 minutes. Remove the paper and beans and bake for a further 5 minutes until pale gold. Leave to cool completely in the tin."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the frangipane and fill"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beat the softened butter and caster sugar together until pale and fluffy. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Fold in the ground almonds, flour, and almond extract. Spread the raspberry jam over the base of the cooled pastry case. Spoon the frangipane over the jam and smooth level. Scatter flaked almonds over the top. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until the frangipane is set and golden and a skewer inserted in the centre comes out with just a few moist crumbs. Cool in the tin, then dust with icing sugar before serving."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
